The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Combating cancer

 A knowledge-based organisation, Cancer Foundation of India (CFI) generates relevant scientific information on preventive aspects of human cancers for the benefit of promoting cancer public health in the country. To mark the completion of three years of public service through its active campaign on cancer control and treatment, CFI hosts a week-long exhibition of photographs on cancer prevention and awareness. Featuring works on the theme of Lifestyle and Risk of Cancer, including 10 photographs from the ABP archives, the show is the first-ever of its kind in our country, spreading the message that a healthy lifestyle holds the key to reducing incidences of cancer and cancer-related deaths. Led by eminent photographer Raghu Rai, the exhibition showcases the works of Abu Naser Siddique, Amit Dhar, Amit Shanker, Anindya Majumdar, Arun Ganguly, Balaram Bose, Bikas Das, Boman Irani, Dilip Banerjee, Fawzan Husain, Ipshita Barua, K.R. Deepak, Krishnendu Halder, Kushal Yadav, Mala Mukherjee, Nitin Rai, Prashanta Biswas, Radha Kanta Pal, Rashid un Nabi, Satyaki Ghosh, Srenik Sett, Surya Sen and Suvendu Chatterjee.

 Event: An exhibition of photographs on cancer awareness

 When: Till November 11, 3 pm - 8 pm

 Where: Academy of Fine Arts, North Gallery




